Program: Discovery
Title: Life Cycles - the rhythm of life
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrytf
Last Broadcast Date: 02 November 2004
Our heart beats, therefore we are. First in a series on the hidden maths that govern the rhythm of life, From the rapid pulsations of the neurons in our brains, to the periodic flowering of bamboo species at 120 year intervals, life's rhythms span an incredible range of scale.